<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Bait1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Bait,</orth> subst., meat to allure fish: <cit><quote>she touched no unknown --s, nor feared no hooks,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 103" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 103</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a swallowed b. on purpose laid to make the taker mad,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 129.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 129, 7</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. pp 53" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.1.28" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 1, 28</bibl>. 33 <cit><quote>(to lay a b.).</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 1.1.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 1, 101</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.2.356" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 2, 356</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.8.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 8, 20</bibl> (F<hi rend="sub">1</hi> <emph>bed,</emph> the other Ff <emph>bit,</emph> which is probably the true reading). <bibl n="shak. cor 4.1.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 1, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.4.91" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 4, 91</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.4.91" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 4, 91</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 2.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 2.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ham 2.1.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 1, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.4.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 4, 59</bibl>.
